{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 30,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 30 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:1",
      "text": "These things says the man to them that trust in God; and I cease.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:2",
      "text": "For I am the most simple of all men, and there is not in me the wisdom of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:3",
      "text": "God has taught me wisdom, and I know the knowledge of the holy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:4",
      "text": "Who has gone up to heaven, and come down? who has gathered the winds in his bosom? who has wrapped up the waters in a garment? who has dominion of all the ends of the earth? what is his name? or what is the name of his children?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:5",
      "text": "For all the words of God are tried in the fire, and he defends those that reverence him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:6",
      "text": "Add not unto his words, lest he reprove thee, and thou be made a liar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:7",
      "text": "Two things I ask of thee; take not favour from me before I die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:8",
      "text": "Remove far from me vanity and falsehood: and give me not wealth or poverty; but appoint me what is needful and sufficient:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:9",
      "text": "lest I be filled and become false, and say, Who sees me? or be poor and steal, and swear vainly by the name of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:10",
      "text": "Deliver not a servant into the hands of his master, lest he curse thee, and thou be utterly destroyed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:11",
      "text": "A wicked generation curse their father, and do not bless their mother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:12",
      "text": "A wicked generation judge themselves to be just, but do not cleanse their way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:13",
      "text": "A wicked generation have lofty eyes, and exalt themselves with their eyelids.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:14",
      "text": "A wicked generation have swords for teeth and jaw-teeth as knives, so as to destroy and devour the lowly from the earth, and the poor of them from among men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:15",
      "text": "The horse-leech had three dearly-beloved daughters: and these three did not satisfy her; and the fourth was not contented so as to say, Enough.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:16",
      "text": "The grave, and the love of a woman, and the earth not filled with water; water also and fire will not say, It is enough.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:17",
      "text": "The eye that laughs to scorn a father, and dishonours the old age of a mother, let the ravens of the valleys pick it out, and let the young eagles devour it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:18",
      "text": "Moreover there are three things impossible for me to comprehend, and the fourth I know not:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:19",
      "text": "the track of a flying eagle; and the ways of a serpent on a rock; and the paths of a ship passing through the sea; and the ways of a man in youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:20",
      "text": "Such is the way of an adulterous woman, who having washed herself from what she has done, says she has done nothing amiss.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:21",
      "text": "By three thing the earth is troubled, and the fourth it cannot bear:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:22",
      "text": "if a servant reign; or a fool be filled with food;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:23",
      "text": "or if a maid-servant should cast out her own mistress; and if a hateful woman should marry a good man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:24",
      "text": "And there are four very little things upon the earth, but these are wiser than the wise:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:25",
      "text": "the ants which are weak, and yet prepare their food in summer;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:26",
      "text": "the rabbits also are a feeble race, who make their houses in the rocks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:27",
      "text": "The locusts have no king, and yet march orderly at one command.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:28",
      "text": "And the eft, which supports itself by its hands, and is easily taken, dwells in the fortresses of kings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:29",
      "text": "And there are three things which go well, and a fourth which passes along finely.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.30",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:30",
      "text": "A lion’s whelp, stronger than all other beasts, which turns not away, nor fears any beast;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.31",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:31",
      "text": "and a cock walking in boldly among the hens, and the goat leading the herd; and a king publicly speaking before a nation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.32",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:32",
      "text": "If thou abandon thyself to mirth, and stretch forth thine hand in a quarrel, thou shalt be disgraced.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.30.33",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:33",
      "text": "Milk out milk, and there shall be butter, and if thou wing one’s nostrils there shall come out blood: so if thou extort words, there will come forth quarrels and strifes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
